WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.390 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.390 --> 00:00:10.780 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:10.780 --> 00:00:20.235 align:middle line:90%


00:00:20.235 --> 00:00:22.360 align:middle line:10%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Well, it's
healthy to be a skeptic,

00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:24.890 align:middle line:10%
but it's even healthier
to be a believer

00:00:24.890 --> 00:00:27.010 align:middle line:10%
after you've checked into facts.

00:00:27.010 --> 00:00:31.545 align:middle line:10%
You'll find that out on
our next "Beyond Belief."

00:00:31.545 --> 00:00:33.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NARRATOR: He is
one of America's most

00:00:33.170 --> 00:00:35.720 align:middle line:84%
prominent skeptics and
perhaps the world's

00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:39.040 align:middle line:84%
only full-time professional,
science-based paranormal

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:39.910 align:middle line:90%
investigator.

00:00:39.910 --> 00:00:42.070 align:middle line:84%
Joe Nickell is a
senior research fellow

00:00:42.070 --> 00:00:44.420 align:middle line:84%
for the community for
skeptical inquiry,

00:00:44.420 --> 00:00:47.502 align:middle line:84%
writes regularly for its
journal, the "Skeptical

00:00:47.502 --> 00:00:50.580 align:middle line:84%
Inquirer," and is an associate
dean of the Center for Inquiry

00:00:50.580 --> 00:00:51.780 align:middle line:90%
Institute.

00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:54.470 align:middle line:84%
The author or editor
of more than 30 books,

00:00:54.470 --> 00:00:56.950 align:middle line:84%
Joe doesn't see
himself as a debunker.

00:00:56.950 --> 00:00:59.320 align:middle line:84%
But so far, he has yet
to uncover any truth

00:00:59.320 --> 00:01:02.330 align:middle line:90%
miracles, ghosts, or monsters.

00:01:02.330 --> 00:01:07.626 align:middle line:84%
He reveals what he has
found today "Beyond Belief."

00:01:07.626 --> 00:01:09.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And one
of Joe Nickell's

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:11.333 align:middle line:84%
books, of course, that he
wrote with Robert Bartholomew,

00:01:11.333 --> 00:01:13.110 align:middle line:84%
"American Hauntings,"
and we're going

00:01:13.110 --> 00:01:14.930 align:middle line:84%
to get into that
in a big way today.

00:01:14.930 --> 00:01:16.162 align:middle line:90%
Joe, welcome to the program.

00:01:16.162 --> 00:01:17.620 align:middle line:84%
>>JOE NICKELL:
Pleasure being here.

00:01:17.620 --> 00:01:20.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did
you, as a skeptic,

00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:24.600 align:middle line:84%
get involved in investigating
paranormal issues?

00:01:24.600 --> 00:01:29.020 align:middle line:10%
>>NICKELL: I grew up as a boy,
like every other boy or girl,

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:32.890 align:middle line:10%
interested in ghosts
and so forth, was

00:01:32.890 --> 00:01:35.300 align:middle line:10%
fascinated by Houdini.

00:01:35.300 --> 00:01:37.050 align:middle line:84%
My father was an
amateur magician,

00:01:37.050 --> 00:01:38.922 align:middle line:90%
so we had magic stuff all--

00:01:38.922 --> 00:01:40.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You love that stuff.

00:01:40.130 --> 00:01:41.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: --from my
earliest memories.

00:01:41.930 --> 00:01:45.210 align:middle line:84%
I later would become
a resident magician

00:01:45.210 --> 00:01:48.670 align:middle line:84%
at the Houdini Hall of
Fame and went on from there

00:01:48.670 --> 00:01:53.680 align:middle line:84%
to work as a detective for a
world famous detective agency

00:01:53.680 --> 00:01:57.430 align:middle line:84%
and somewhat later in life
got a master's and doctorate

00:01:57.430 --> 00:01:59.460 align:middle line:84%
in English literature
and folklore.

00:01:59.460 --> 00:02:00.420 align:middle line:90%
So it's an odd mix.

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:01.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You mixed
them all, though.

00:02:01.920 --> 00:02:03.350 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: But it works for me.

00:02:03.350 --> 00:02:05.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a scientist,
but I've always

00:02:05.340 --> 00:02:09.320 align:middle line:90%
been sort of a forensic buff.

00:02:09.320 --> 00:02:11.780 align:middle line:84%
And I'm co-author of the
book "Crime Science."

00:02:11.780 --> 00:02:16.010 align:middle line:84%
So if I need a real scientist,
of course, I go get one.

00:02:16.010 --> 00:02:19.100 align:middle line:84%
But it's a great mix, and
it's all very interesting.

00:02:19.100 --> 00:02:23.720 align:middle line:84%
And I found out long
ago that it might

00:02:23.720 --> 00:02:25.370 align:middle line:84%
be fun to believe
something, or it

00:02:25.370 --> 00:02:28.770 align:middle line:84%
might be fun to make
fun of something silly.

00:02:28.770 --> 00:02:32.030 align:middle line:84%
What was really interesting
was to actually try

00:02:32.030 --> 00:02:33.720 align:middle line:90%
to solve a mystery.

00:02:33.720 --> 00:02:37.210 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing that
even comes close to that

00:02:37.210 --> 00:02:40.067 align:middle line:84%
as a satisfying
personal accomplishment.

00:02:40.067 --> 00:02:41.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That excites
you a lot, doesn't it?

00:02:41.900 --> 00:02:42.700 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: It does.

00:02:42.700 --> 00:02:45.760 align:middle line:84%
And I found out-- I've done
literary detective work,

00:02:45.760 --> 00:02:48.450 align:middle line:84%
historical,
forensic, paranormal,

00:02:48.450 --> 00:02:52.190 align:middle line:84%
and I don't care-- I don't
much care what the topic is.

00:02:52.190 --> 00:02:55.040 align:middle line:84%
If it's interesting,
mysterious, and if I

00:02:55.040 --> 00:02:59.350 align:middle line:84%
think I might have a
chance to solve it, I'm in.

00:02:59.350 --> 00:03:02.350 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Joe, a lot of people
confuse the word skeptic.

00:03:02.350 --> 00:03:05.290 align:middle line:84%
Because they think a
skeptic is a nonbeliever.

00:03:05.290 --> 00:03:07.900 align:middle line:84%
My definition of a
skeptic is someone

00:03:07.900 --> 00:03:12.570 align:middle line:84%
who wants to find the
facts before he decides

00:03:12.570 --> 00:03:14.120 align:middle line:90%
whether to believe or not.

00:03:14.120 --> 00:03:14.935 align:middle line:90%
Is that true?

00:03:14.935 --> 00:03:15.810 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: That's it.

00:03:15.810 --> 00:03:19.000 align:middle line:84%
You really have to-- I mean, you
could be skeptical of anything.

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:23.130 align:middle line:84%
There are people with misplaced
skepticism about, let's say,

00:03:23.130 --> 00:03:25.540 align:middle line:90%
the Holocaust or global warming.

00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:28.960 align:middle line:84%
What we need is we
need to have skepticism

00:03:28.960 --> 00:03:32.460 align:middle line:84%
to those things to
which skepticism is due,

00:03:32.460 --> 00:03:35.410 align:middle line:84%
meaning those things that
appear on the face of it

00:03:35.410 --> 00:03:38.420 align:middle line:84%
to be far fetched or appear
to contradict science.

00:03:38.420 --> 00:03:41.630 align:middle line:84%
They may be legit, but
they're sort of warning signs

00:03:41.630 --> 00:03:44.520 align:middle line:84%
or they kind of need
to be checked out.

00:03:44.520 --> 00:03:47.280 align:middle line:84%
And so if we're skeptical
of those things,

00:03:47.280 --> 00:03:52.010 align:middle line:84%
that's just the natural
correct attitude of mind.

00:03:52.010 --> 00:03:53.510 align:middle line:90%
And it doesn't prejudge.

00:03:53.510 --> 00:03:56.590 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't say that
something isn't

00:03:56.590 --> 00:03:59.810 align:middle line:90%
true to question, oh, really?

00:03:59.810 --> 00:04:04.210 align:middle line:84%
I remember Coleridge, the
famous literary figure,

00:04:04.210 --> 00:04:07.470 align:middle line:84%
and he had this term he used
called "the willing suspension

00:04:07.470 --> 00:04:09.247 align:middle line:90%
of disbelief."

00:04:09.247 --> 00:04:11.080 align:middle line:84%
In other words, you
don't sit in the theater

00:04:11.080 --> 00:04:13.490 align:middle line:84%
and nudge your friend and say,
those aren't real bullets.

00:04:13.490 --> 00:04:15.580 align:middle line:90%
He didn't really kill her.

00:04:15.580 --> 00:04:18.060 align:middle line:90%
Because that's just annoying.

00:04:18.060 --> 00:04:19.680 align:middle line:90%
The same in the paranormal.

00:04:19.680 --> 00:04:25.550 align:middle line:84%
We need to put aside the sort
of belief-disbelief question

00:04:25.550 --> 00:04:30.610 align:middle line:84%
for the time being, go to the
haunted house or whatever,

00:04:30.610 --> 00:04:33.880 align:middle line:84%
and ask ourselves, what
really happened here?

00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:34.790 align:middle line:90%
How do we know that?

00:04:34.790 --> 00:04:35.640 align:middle line:90%
Are we sure?

00:04:35.640 --> 00:04:37.990 align:middle line:84%
Is that a fact,
or is that a piece

00:04:37.990 --> 00:04:40.920 align:middle line:84%
of false information
somebody made up?

00:04:40.920 --> 00:04:44.140 align:middle line:84%
And then when we
can get the facts,

00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:47.390 align:middle line:84%
we might have a chance to
find out what really happened.

00:04:47.390 --> 00:04:50.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Joe, if you
can't get the facts,

00:04:50.140 --> 00:04:52.800 align:middle line:84%
because it's difficult--
let's talk about God for now.

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:56.550 align:middle line:84%
It's very difficult to
prove the existence of God

00:04:56.550 --> 00:04:57.509 align:middle line:90%
with evidence and fact.

00:04:57.509 --> 00:04:58.424 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: It is hard.

00:04:58.424 --> 00:05:00.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So what do
you do about that?

00:05:00.010 --> 00:05:03.630 align:middle line:84%
Do you stay a skeptic
and say there is no God?

00:05:03.630 --> 00:05:05.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: I tend
to take the position

00:05:05.410 --> 00:05:08.770 align:middle line:84%
that if there is
not evidence for it,

00:05:08.770 --> 00:05:11.380 align:middle line:84%
then I just remain
skeptical of it.

00:05:11.380 --> 00:05:14.040 align:middle line:84%
In other words, I wouldn't
try to convince you

00:05:14.040 --> 00:05:15.410 align:middle line:90%
that there are no leprechauns.

00:05:15.410 --> 00:05:18.130 align:middle line:90%
I mean, how would we do that?

00:05:18.130 --> 00:05:20.470 align:middle line:84%
I have a standing offer if
somebody wants to finance--

00:05:20.470 --> 00:05:20.915 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Let's go to Ireland.

00:05:20.915 --> 00:05:21.300 align:middle line:90%
Let's do it.

00:05:21.300 --> 00:05:23.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: Yeah, if they want
to finance my expedition,

00:05:23.180 --> 00:05:24.363 align:middle line:90%
George and I will go.

00:05:24.363 --> 00:05:25.290 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We'll go.

00:05:25.290 --> 00:05:26.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: We'll go to Ireland,
and we'll beat the bushes,

00:05:26.910 --> 00:05:28.804 align:middle line:84%
and we'll say, no,
no leprechauns.

00:05:28.804 --> 00:05:30.470 align:middle line:84%
And somebody will
say, ah, but don't you

00:05:30.470 --> 00:05:33.090 align:middle line:84%
know that we creatures are
mostly around Blarney Castle,

00:05:33.090 --> 00:05:34.050 align:middle line:90%
don't you know?

00:05:34.050 --> 00:05:35.020 align:middle line:90%
OK, fine.

00:05:35.020 --> 00:05:35.830 align:middle line:90%
We'll go back.

00:05:35.830 --> 00:05:37.590 align:middle line:84%
We may have to have
a few more drinks.

00:05:37.590 --> 00:05:40.790 align:middle line:84%
We'll have a good time,
no, no leprechauns.

00:05:40.790 --> 00:05:42.780 align:middle line:84%
Ah, but don't you know
that we creatures have

00:05:42.780 --> 00:05:45.310 align:middle line:84%
the power of invisibility,
don't you know?

00:05:45.310 --> 00:05:46.290 align:middle line:90%
Well, at some point--

00:05:46.290 --> 00:05:47.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: [INAUDIBLE] I'm
standing right next to you,

00:05:47.940 --> 00:05:48.950 align:middle line:90%
man, right?

00:05:48.950 --> 00:05:50.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: [LAUGHING]
So what we have

00:05:50.810 --> 00:05:53.420 align:middle line:84%
to do-- I can't prove
there are no leprechauns.

00:05:53.420 --> 00:05:57.250 align:middle line:84%
I just assume that until
somebody brings me--

00:05:57.250 --> 00:05:59.360 align:middle line:84%
I hate to say this,
George-- a dead leprechaun--

00:05:59.360 --> 00:06:00.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh!

00:06:00.160 --> 00:06:01.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: Oh, I
shouldn't have said that.

00:06:01.910 --> 00:06:03.249 align:middle line:90%
I know I'll be hated now.

00:06:03.249 --> 00:06:04.290 align:middle line:90%
All the school children--

00:06:04.290 --> 00:06:05.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I thought
they lived forever.

00:06:05.940 --> 00:06:07.231 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: Well, maybe they do.

00:06:07.231 --> 00:06:08.600 align:middle line:90%
But you see my point.

00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:12.020 align:middle line:84%
Unless we have some really
good evidence that science

00:06:12.020 --> 00:06:13.880 align:middle line:90%
could really get into--

00:06:13.880 --> 00:06:14.880 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And back it up.

00:06:14.880 --> 00:06:16.546 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: --then we
just don't believe.

00:06:16.546 --> 00:06:18.630 align:middle line:84%
It's not a question of
proving there isn't a God

00:06:18.630 --> 00:06:20.150 align:middle line:90%
or proving there aren't angels.

00:06:20.150 --> 00:06:22.770 align:middle line:90%
I just don't bother doing that.

00:06:22.770 --> 00:06:26.810 align:middle line:84%
I say, well, we can
explain the world and most

00:06:26.810 --> 00:06:29.370 align:middle line:84%
of the phenomena in the
world without recourse

00:06:29.370 --> 00:06:30.560 align:middle line:90%
to any supernatural.

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:35.390 align:middle line:84%
So I just have no belief
in the supernatural.

00:06:35.390 --> 00:06:37.510 align:middle line:84%
But it would be folly
for me to attempt

00:06:37.510 --> 00:06:38.797 align:middle line:90%
to disprove all those things.

00:06:38.797 --> 00:06:40.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, let's
talk a little bit

00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:42.170 align:middle line:84%
about some of your
investigations

00:06:42.170 --> 00:06:45.420 align:middle line:84%
into the paranormal world
that you highlight in the book

00:06:45.420 --> 00:06:47.270 align:middle line:90%
"American Hauntings," of course.

00:06:47.270 --> 00:06:51.600 align:middle line:84%
What we do is we look at several
cases in the book, including,

00:06:51.600 --> 00:06:56.827 align:middle line:84%
of course, one of my
favorites, "The Exorcist."

00:06:56.827 --> 00:07:00.960 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:00.960 --> 00:07:01.970 align:middle line:90%
>>My bed was shaking.

00:07:01.970 --> 00:07:07.316 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:07.316 --> 00:07:10.718 align:middle line:90%


00:07:10.718 --> 00:07:13.650 align:middle line:84%
>>Do you think I should
take her to a psychiatrist?

00:07:13.650 --> 00:07:17.640 align:middle line:84%
>>The problem with your
daughter is not her bed.

00:07:17.640 --> 00:07:19.132 align:middle line:90%
It's her brain.

00:07:19.132 --> 00:07:22.018 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:22.018 --> 00:07:23.942 align:middle line:90%
>>[GROUP SINGING]

00:07:23.942 --> 00:07:26.609 align:middle line:90%
>>I think we've got a guest.

00:07:26.609 --> 00:07:27.775 align:middle line:90%
>>You're gonna die up there.

00:07:27.775 --> 00:07:29.755 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:29.755 --> 00:07:30.745 align:middle line:90%
>>Mother!

00:07:30.745 --> 00:07:32.230 align:middle line:90%
Mother!

00:07:32.230 --> 00:07:34.400 align:middle line:90%
Mother!

00:07:34.400 --> 00:07:35.200 align:middle line:90%
Mother!

00:07:35.200 --> 00:07:36.685 align:middle line:90%
[SCREAMING]

00:07:36.685 --> 00:07:38.940 align:middle line:90%
I don't want it!

00:07:38.940 --> 00:07:42.142 align:middle line:90%
>>Honey, it's to help you!

00:07:42.142 --> 00:07:44.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're gonna
feel a little stick here.

00:07:44.100 --> 00:07:49.412 align:middle line:90%


00:07:49.412 --> 00:07:51.230 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: Why this girl?

00:07:51.230 --> 00:07:53.418 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't make sense.

00:07:53.418 --> 00:07:54.720 align:middle line:90%
>>Please, Mother!

00:07:54.720 --> 00:07:55.894 align:middle line:90%
Make it stop!

00:07:55.894 --> 00:07:57.130 align:middle line:90%
It's burning!

00:07:57.130 --> 00:07:59.965 align:middle line:90%
Make it-- [GROWLING]

00:07:59.965 --> 00:08:01.340 align:middle line:84%
>>You tell me you
know for a fact

00:08:01.340 --> 00:08:03.250 align:middle line:84%
that an exorcism
wouldn't do any good!

00:08:03.250 --> 00:08:05.060 align:middle line:90%
You tell me that!

00:08:05.060 --> 00:08:05.930 align:middle line:90%
>>The sow is mine!

00:08:05.930 --> 00:08:09.135 align:middle line:90%
[GROWLING]

00:08:09.135 --> 00:08:11.530 align:middle line:90%
>>You know what she did.

00:08:11.530 --> 00:08:14.404 align:middle line:90%
[GROWLING]

00:08:14.404 --> 00:08:16.320 align:middle line:90%
[SCREAMING]

00:08:16.320 --> 00:08:17.280 align:middle line:90%
>>Help her!

00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:19.230 align:middle line:90%
Help her!

00:08:19.230 --> 00:08:23.490 align:middle line:84%
>>The power of
Christ compels you!

00:08:23.490 --> 00:08:27.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: OK, that was Linda
Blair in "The Exorcist."

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:31.460 align:middle line:84%
The real story was a little boy
from Baltimore, Maryland, ended

00:08:31.460 --> 00:08:32.812 align:middle line:90%
up in St. Louis.

00:08:32.812 --> 00:08:33.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: Boy named R.

00:08:33.770 --> 00:08:35.269 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Where those
priests that I,

00:08:35.269 --> 00:08:38.120 align:middle line:84%
for the rest of my career,
tried to interview.

00:08:38.120 --> 00:08:39.350 align:middle line:90%
One refused.

00:08:39.350 --> 00:08:40.340 align:middle line:90%
The other has died.

00:08:40.340 --> 00:08:42.010 align:middle line:90%
Now the other one has died.

00:08:42.010 --> 00:08:43.929 align:middle line:84%
We were never able
to get to him.

00:08:43.929 --> 00:08:48.130 align:middle line:84%
But something horrendous
happened in that hospital

00:08:48.130 --> 00:08:50.320 align:middle line:84%
where that little
boy was exorcised.

00:08:50.320 --> 00:08:52.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: Actually, one of
the priests kept a diary.

00:08:52.570 --> 00:08:57.000 align:middle line:84%
And that diary has been
available and published.

00:08:57.000 --> 00:08:59.020 align:middle line:84%
And I went through that
with some interest,

00:08:59.020 --> 00:09:03.310 align:middle line:84%
trying to look at it from my
magician's background, what

00:09:03.310 --> 00:09:04.940 align:middle line:90%
exactly was happening.

00:09:04.940 --> 00:09:07.000 align:middle line:84%
And that case really
started out as a kind

00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:09.690 align:middle line:84%
of poltergeist
case, some mischief,

00:09:09.690 --> 00:09:12.790 align:middle line:84%
some odd things thrown
about or whatever.

00:09:12.790 --> 00:09:17.600 align:middle line:84%
And it gradually became more
of something sinister and--

00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:18.400 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Evil.

00:09:18.400 --> 00:09:21.510 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: Yeah, evil,
and took on-- it evolved,

00:09:21.510 --> 00:09:23.970 align:middle line:84%
in other words, which
makes me suspicious

00:09:23.970 --> 00:09:26.920 align:middle line:84%
of it being a
genuine phenomenon.

00:09:26.920 --> 00:09:29.175 align:middle line:84%
The boy was at the
center for everything,

00:09:29.175 --> 00:09:31.730 align:middle line:84%
as is the case
with poltergeists.

00:09:31.730 --> 00:09:37.120 align:middle line:84%
That is, nothing happened
if he wasn't around.

00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:40.600 align:middle line:84%
And he would produce
these markings.

00:09:40.600 --> 00:09:43.290 align:middle line:84%
Words would be
scratched on his body.

00:09:43.290 --> 00:09:46.680 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, people thought,
he couldn't be doing this.

00:09:46.680 --> 00:09:51.080 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, he was actually
caught once doing it.

00:09:51.080 --> 00:09:52.950 align:middle line:84%
And then you see
the rationalizations

00:09:52.950 --> 00:09:55.730 align:middle line:84%
of the believers, saying,
yeah, but he was just imitating

00:09:55.730 --> 00:09:56.950 align:middle line:90%
what the real demons did.

00:09:56.950 --> 00:10:00.530 align:middle line:84%
No, see, when anybody's
caught faking something,

00:10:00.530 --> 00:10:02.995 align:middle line:84%
I'm pretty well ready to just
close the case right there.

00:10:02.995 --> 00:10:04.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's it
for you right there.

00:10:04.620 --> 00:10:07.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: So that
case, if you go back

00:10:07.090 --> 00:10:10.140 align:middle line:84%
and you cut through all
the exaggerations, all

00:10:10.140 --> 00:10:14.480 align:middle line:84%
the elaborations and stuff, and
look at what really happened,

00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:17.790 align:middle line:84%
most of it was stuff
that a boy could

00:10:17.790 --> 00:10:21.880 align:middle line:84%
and apparently did do,
nothing supernatural.

00:10:21.880 --> 00:10:26.080 align:middle line:84%
People were trying to impose
on that layers of claims

00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:27.490 align:middle line:90%
that just don't hold water.

00:10:27.490 --> 00:10:30.090 align:middle line:84%
I've written
extensively about it,

00:10:30.090 --> 00:10:32.240 align:middle line:84%
and I just think
that people are going

00:10:32.240 --> 00:10:34.290 align:middle line:84%
to have to find a
better case if they

00:10:34.290 --> 00:10:36.010 align:middle line:90%
want to prove the supernatural.

00:10:36.010 --> 00:10:38.740 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Was the boy
doing it for attention?

00:10:38.740 --> 00:10:41.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: This is the
most difficult part

00:10:41.170 --> 00:10:45.060 align:middle line:84%
of some of these cases is
trying to get at motive.

00:10:45.060 --> 00:10:49.780 align:middle line:84%
It's easy enough to say, OK,
we caught So-and-So red-handed.

00:10:49.780 --> 00:10:51.692 align:middle line:90%
Why was he doing it?

00:10:51.692 --> 00:10:53.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's he
gaining from it?

00:10:53.150 --> 00:10:54.691 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: The kid
often doesn't even

00:10:54.691 --> 00:10:56.470 align:middle line:90%
know himself why he's doing it.

00:10:56.470 --> 00:10:59.610 align:middle line:84%
It could be a combination
of the difficulties

00:10:59.610 --> 00:11:02.815 align:middle line:84%
of going through puberty,
family situations.

00:11:02.815 --> 00:11:04.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Mentally
disturbed, pressure.

00:11:04.730 --> 00:11:05.930 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: Exactly.

00:11:05.930 --> 00:11:09.680 align:middle line:84%
Subconscious motivations,
desire for attention

00:11:09.680 --> 00:11:13.360 align:middle line:84%
without really being aware
of what you're doing.

00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:17.720 align:middle line:84%
Just boredom can produce
a great deal of mischief

00:11:17.720 --> 00:11:19.970 align:middle line:90%
from kids-- just boredom.

00:11:19.970 --> 00:11:21.950 align:middle line:90%
They find that if--

00:11:21.950 --> 00:11:23.200 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Even during that era?

00:11:23.200 --> 00:11:23.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: Yeah.

00:11:23.860 --> 00:11:24.660 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:24.660 --> 00:11:31.190 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that that case--
and it spills over to movies

00:11:31.190 --> 00:11:34.440 align:middle line:84%
like the "Poltergeist,"
"Amityville Horror,"

00:11:34.440 --> 00:11:35.300 align:middle line:90%
"The Conjuring"--

00:11:35.300 --> 00:11:35.490 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:11:35.490 --> 00:11:37.134 align:middle line:90%
We'll get into all off that.

00:11:37.134 --> 00:11:38.550 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: Not so
much Amityville,

00:11:38.550 --> 00:11:44.170 align:middle line:84%
because Amityville really
wasn't kids acting up primarily.

00:11:44.170 --> 00:11:46.780 align:middle line:90%
Amityville was a hoax.

00:11:46.780 --> 00:11:48.880 align:middle line:84%
And it was not the
"Amityville Horror."

00:11:48.880 --> 00:11:51.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, let's look at
a clip on that, "Amityville

00:11:51.610 --> 00:11:54.253 align:middle line:90%
Horror," from the movie.

