[THUNDER CLAPPING]

00:13:05.950 --> 00:13:09.384 align:middle line:84%
>>28 days after the Lutz family
moved into their dream house--

00:13:09.384 --> 00:13:11.272 align:middle line:90%
[GLASS BREAKING]

00:13:11.272 --> 00:13:13.720 align:middle line:84%
--they were running
for their lives.

00:13:13.720 --> 00:13:17.850 align:middle line:84%
What happened to them is
an experience in terror

00:13:17.850 --> 00:13:19.502 align:middle line:90%
you will never forget.

00:13:19.502 --> 00:13:23.165 align:middle line:84%
And you will believe in
the Amityville Horror.

00:13:23.165 --> 00:13:25.054 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:25.054 --> 00:13:26.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: OK, what
do you say, Joe,

00:13:26.470 --> 00:13:28.870 align:middle line:90%
that this episode was a hoax?

00:13:28.870 --> 00:13:30.670 align:middle line:90%
The murders were real.

00:13:30.670 --> 00:13:32.130 align:middle line:90%
They happened in that house.

00:13:32.130 --> 00:13:32.940 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: Right.

00:13:32.940 --> 00:13:36.100 align:middle line:84%
Ronald DeFeo absolutely
murdered his parents

00:13:36.100 --> 00:13:39.220 align:middle line:90%
and his siblings in that house.

00:13:39.220 --> 00:13:41.750 align:middle line:90%
And that horror was real.

00:13:41.750 --> 00:13:45.500 align:middle line:84%
But when George and
Kathy Lutz came in later,

00:13:45.500 --> 00:13:48.970 align:middle line:84%
apparently looking for
book and movie deals,

00:13:48.970 --> 00:13:52.230 align:middle line:84%
they didn't seem to really have
plans to really stay there very

00:13:52.230 --> 00:13:54.940 align:middle line:90%
long and didn't have the money.

00:13:54.940 --> 00:13:58.420 align:middle line:84%
When I first heard the case
of the Amityville Horror,

00:13:58.420 --> 00:14:02.140 align:middle line:84%
and I had by that point a lot
of experience with such cases,

00:14:02.140 --> 00:14:04.820 align:middle line:84%
it sounded a little bit
like a traditional haunting,

00:14:04.820 --> 00:14:08.390 align:middle line:84%
a little bit like a poltergeist,
a little bit like a demon.

00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:11.480 align:middle line:84%
It was such a hodgepodge it
was like if you and I decided

00:14:11.480 --> 00:14:12.620 align:middle line:90%
to make up a case.

00:14:12.620 --> 00:14:14.640 align:middle line:84%
We put a little bit
of each ingredient

00:14:14.640 --> 00:14:16.770 align:middle line:84%
in because it would make
it more interesting.

00:14:16.770 --> 00:14:20.690 align:middle line:84%
I had never seen a case of
that type, that admixture.

00:14:20.690 --> 00:14:22.460 align:middle line:90%
I'd never seen anything like it.

00:14:22.460 --> 00:14:25.610 align:middle line:84%
Pretty quickly you could show
that some of the things that

00:14:25.610 --> 00:14:27.370 align:middle line:90%
were claimed didn't happen.

00:14:27.370 --> 00:14:30.739 align:middle line:84%
For example, the devil's
tracks in the snow

00:14:30.739 --> 00:14:32.280 align:middle line:84%
couldn't have
happened, because there

00:14:32.280 --> 00:14:35.660 align:middle line:84%
was no snow on the
ground on those dates.

00:14:35.660 --> 00:14:40.190 align:middle line:84%
And I knew Barbara Cromarty,
who lived in the house later,

00:14:40.190 --> 00:14:42.710 align:middle line:84%
and she could take
you around the house

00:14:42.710 --> 00:14:45.910 align:middle line:84%
and show you that some of
the windows and doors that

00:14:45.910 --> 00:14:49.340 align:middle line:84%
were supposedly ripped off their
hinges by demonic forces, that

00:14:49.340 --> 00:14:50.460 align:middle line:90%
never happened.

00:14:50.460 --> 00:14:52.410 align:middle line:84%
The old hardware
was still there.

00:14:52.410 --> 00:14:53.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's disappointing.

00:14:53.660 --> 00:14:55.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NICKELL: The old
varnish in place.

00:14:55.450 --> 00:14:58.370 align:middle line:84%
No locksmiths had ever
been called to the house.

00:14:58.370 --> 00:15:01.767 align:middle line:84%
The police said they
never were called.

00:15:01.767 --> 00:15:03.350 align:middle line:84%
Surprise to people
who watch the movie

00:15:03.350 --> 00:15:05.700 align:middle line:84%
and read the book, because
they're convinced the police

00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:07.476 align:middle line:84%
came and the priest
came and stuff.

00:15:07.476 --> 00:15:08.350 align:middle line:90%
That was all made up.

00:15:08.350 --> 00:15:10.141 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So you think
the whole thing other

00:15:10.141 --> 00:15:13.360 align:middle line:84%
than the murders was all
made up to make money.

00:15:13.360 --> 00:15:14.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: Pretty much.

00:15:14.330 --> 00:15:15.130 align:middle line:90%
Pretty much.

00:15:15.130 --> 00:15:24.150 align:middle line:84%
Because Ronald DeFeo's attorney
William Weber testified.

00:15:24.150 --> 00:15:26.360 align:middle line:84%
He came forward
and actually said

00:15:26.360 --> 00:15:30.260 align:middle line:84%
that those horror
incidents were made up

00:15:30.260 --> 00:15:35.280 align:middle line:84%
over several bottles of
wine in his law office, wine

00:15:35.280 --> 00:15:37.770 align:middle line:90%
that George Lutz was drinking.

00:15:37.770 --> 00:15:39.070 align:middle line:90%
And they were making this up.

00:15:39.070 --> 00:15:40.710 align:middle line:90%
Now, why was Weber doing this?

00:15:40.710 --> 00:15:45.460 align:middle line:84%
Well, he thought if there
was any kind of demonic story

00:15:45.460 --> 00:15:49.340 align:middle line:84%
and people believed that demons
were kind of possessing people,

00:15:49.340 --> 00:15:53.465 align:middle line:84%
maybe he could get a new trial
for his client, the murderer.

00:15:53.465 --> 00:15:55.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What lawyer would
want to get a client off

00:15:55.590 --> 00:15:57.900 align:middle line:84%
when he knew they were--
well, that's another story.

00:15:57.900 --> 00:15:59.440 align:middle line:90%
>>NICKELL: It's just bizarre.

00:15:59.440 --> 00:16:02.590 align:middle line:84%
But there is Weber
having confessed.

00:16:02.590 --> 00:16:03.930 align:middle line:90%
It's well known.

00:16:03.930 --> 00:16:06.540 align:middle line:84%
And the Cromartys
sued because they

00:16:06.540 --> 00:16:09.180 align:middle line:90%
couldn't have peace of mind.

00:16:09.180 --> 00:16:12.180 align:middle line:84%
